The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Texmaco net profit jumps
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Texmaco net profit jumps
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, May 16: KK Birla group company Texmaco Ltd today reported a 143 per cent growth rate in net profit at Rs 69.09 crore in 2007-08 against Rs 29.22 crore in the previous year. The company clocked a sales turnover of Rs 937.18 crore during the reporting period.         
	The Texmaco board has recommended a 75 per cent dividend to shareholders.         
	The board also approved splitting Texmacos equity shares of a face value of Rs 10 into 10 shares of Re 1 each.        
	The company registered a net profit of Rs 30.64 crore in the quarter ended March 31 compared with Rs 11.16 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal, a 174.5 per cent rise.         
	Sales during the quarter increased 107.6 per cent to Rs 307.27 crore from Rs 148.03 crore a year ago.        
	A large part of Texmacos improved earnings can be attributed to the over 200 per cent growth in other income.                                                                                                                                      
